ðŸŸ© Problem
Youâ€™re building a stack-based simulation for an airportâ€™s baggage system.
Each operation affects a stack that can hold up to 100 containers.

Supported commands:
- Push X
- Pop
- Top
- IsEmpty
- Size
If Pop or Top is called on an empty stack â†’ print "Stack Underflow".

ðŸŸ© Sample Input
8
Push 10
Push 20
Top
Pop
Top
Size
Pop
IsEmpty

ðŸŸ© Sample Output
20
10
1
true

ðŸŸ© Solution (Array-based Stack)

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        int n = sc.nextInt();
        sc.nextLine();

        int[] stack = new int[100];
        int top = -1;

        while (n > 0) {
            n--;
            String line = sc.nextLine();
            String[] arr = line.trim().split(" ");

            String cmd = arr[0];

            switch (cmd) {

                case "Push":
                    int val = Integer.parseInt(arr[1]);
                    if (top < 99) {
                        stack[++top] = val;
                    }
                    break;

                case "Pop":
                    if (top == -1) {
                        System.out.println("Stack Underflow");
                    } else {
                        top--;
                    }
                    break;

                case "Top":
                    if (top == -1) {
                        System.out.println("Stack Underflow");
                    } else {
                        System.out.println(stack[top]);
                    }
                    break;

                case "IsEmpty":
                    System.out.println(top == -1 ? "true" : "false");
                    break;

                case "Size":
                    System.out.println(top + 1);
                    break;
            }
        }
    }
}


ðŸŸ© Time Complexity -Each operation runs in O(1) ---> Total for N commands â†’ O(N)
ðŸŸ© Space Complexity - Uses fixed array of size 100 â†’ O(1)
